OpenSigne Darija retains the following third-party dataset records for attribution
and license provenance. They are historical evaluation records, not active runtime
registrations or declarations about the provenance of the current local corpus.

Mendeley Data: "A Dataset for Moroccan Sign Language (MoSL)", Version 1,
DOI 10.17632/23phgyt3mt.1, by FATIMA BEN ZAID, Mohamed BENADDY, and
Abdelbasset BOUKDIR. The cited Mendeley release is recorded as CC BY 4.0.
Related article DOI 10.1016/j.dib.2025.112395 documents that release and is not
a second dataset source.

Kaggle: `walidlasseg/moroccan-sign-language-lsm-alphabet-dataset`. Its license
remains UNCONFIRMED in this repository, so no permission to train on or
redistribute that dataset is asserted.

The current core has no external-dataset downloader, archive importer, runtime
source registry, or external-dataset API. Neither cited public dataset is an
active training input. Active model work reads only the already-local 2,216-video
corpus under `ml/data/external/mosl-video-dataset/`; equivalence between that
local corpus and the cited Mendeley release is UNCONFIRMED, so the Mendeley
license must not be inferred for the local files without separate verification.
